CustomerMemo.value: The tune up turned out great!  The new derailleur and cable made the bike shift awesome. The front and rear derailleur cables were greased at the BB guide, the front cable is not creaking anymore and I also noticed that the cable was routed under the nub on the front derailleur by the pinch bolt. This will allow it to us that nub as a leverage point which should make it shift easier for you. The rear wheel was slightly out of dish, I re dished the wheel and added tension to both the driveside and non driveside spokes. The wheel is a lot stronger now.  The only thing I could recommend is a new rear brake cable to make it feel as easy as the front brake caliper, that would cost $3 for the cable and $5 for install. The bike is ready to attack the road once again!
